parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The ABS engages at low speeds
the brake pedal stiffens
the vehicle experiences a complete loss of braking power
the ABS activates on dry pavement
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rotor Failure due to Rust and Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rotors can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The rotors flake and pit apart
causing failure of the brakes
the rotors are warped
the brake pads are worn out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel speed sensor can cause the ABS to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The ABS activates at low speeds
the vehicle experiences a complete loss of braking power
the wheel speed sensor is corroded or rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intermediate steering column shaft can cause a clunking noise, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents due to misdiagnosis of the issue.
symptoms: Constant clunking noise
rattling noise from the steering shaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause loss of steering and brakes, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Shaft breakage on the pump
loss of steering
loss of brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod ball joint can cause loss of control or accidents due to the sudden failure of the steering system.
symptoms: The stud coming out of the ball joint of the tie rod snaps at the ball joint.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tailgate support cables can cause the tailgate to fall, potentially leading to injuries or accidents, especially when the vehicle is loaded or when people are standing near the rear of the truck.
symptoms: The tailgate support cables break or fail
causing the tailgate to fall or drop suddenly
potentially resulting in damage to the vehicle or injury to people nearby.
